## Terms

**The word list is copyleft.** БГ Офис licenses its data explicitly, not just its code —
<https://bgoffice.sourceforge.net/license.html> states that «класифицираните думи» (the
classified words themselves) are under the GNU GPL v2 or later. A 2010 re-licensing of the
distributed spellcheck packages made them available under a **disjunctive tri-licence**:

> GPL-2.0-or-later **OR** LGPL-2.0-or-later **OR** MPL-1.1

which is precisely why the BG Office dictionary can ship inside Firefox and Chrome at all. It is
the same election Debian's `hunspell-bg` and npm's `dictionary-bg` make.

**We take that offer and elect the MPL-1.1.** `data/stress-dict.txt` is distributed under the
Mozilla Public License 1.1, whose full text is in `data/LICENSE-MPL-1.1.txt`.

In practice that means: **improvements to the dictionary file must flow back** under the same
licence, and nothing else in this repository is affected. If you fix a stress mark, that fix stays
free. That seems like the right deal for a dictionary.

This does not affect the extension's own code, which stays MIT (see LICENSE): the tri-licence is
what makes a copyleft data file shippable alongside permissive code, and it is the same route
`hunspell-bg` and `dictionary-bg` take.

**The stress marks themselves** are the one layer with no upstream licence. They come from Речко,
which publishes its database for download (<https://rechnik.chitanka.info/about>: «Скриптовете и
базата са достъпни за сваляне») but states no terms at all. Two things are worth saying plainly:

- A stress position on a word is a *fact*. Facts are not copyrightable; only an original selection
  or arrangement is (Directive 96/9/EC Art. 3(1)), and a list of every word in a language sorted
  alphabetically is not an original selection.
- The EU *sui generis* database right (Art. 7) is a separate matter and does reach substantial
  extraction regardless of originality. Its term is 15 years from first making available
  (Art. 10); the Речко dump has not been regenerated since 2013.

We credit Речко, we do not redistribute its definitions (only word forms and stress positions),
and we would remove the data on a reasonable request from its maintainers.

